[00:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Last year, our viral Mark&nbsp; launch blew the internet away. A bookmark that kept track of what you\'re reading. But amidst all the noise, we&nbsp; wanted to create something that truly felt like it was built for you. I\'m Eason, founder of Mark.'

[00:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And over the past year, we listened to all of your feedback&nbsp; and redesigned Mark from the ground up. This is Mark II. A better tool for collecting&nbsp; your ideas when reading. It highlights passages, records your thoughts,'

[00:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and builds a personal library of&nbsp; everything you choose to keep. It goes wherever your book&nbsp; goes, and it comes in two parts bookmark and highlighter.'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Bookmark lives in the book. And with customization, it\'s a great&nbsp; way to show the world your taste. Highlighter is where magic happens. It has a scanner, allowing you&nbsp; to save your favorite quotes'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and a voice recorder for your favorite ideas, allowing you to engage with your&nbsp; reading without leaving the moment. Everything is off by default, and only turns on when you decide you&nbsp; want to save an idea that\'s worth keeping.'

[01:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And with a single charge, it\'ll&nbsp; last you through a good book. The Mark app is where all of&nbsp; your quotes and ideas live. Every quote knows exactly what book itâ€™s from, and every thought is sorted&nbsp; by the ideas inside of it.'

[01:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'You can search for half remembered&nbsp; quotes from a few months ago. And over time, the app starts&nbsp; drawing patterns across your reading. When you sit down to write&nbsp; a blog post, draft an essay, or just want to think about&nbsp; what you\'ve been reading,'

[01:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'everything is already collected,&nbsp; ready for you to revisit. With Mark, you can read anywhere. Mark saves your highlights&nbsp; and ideas completely offline, and syncs with your phone&nbsp; whenever it is back in range.'

[01:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'We believe something special happens&nbsp; when you sit down with a book and truly immerse yourself in it. And that\'s something you can\'t get from&nbsp; quick dopamine hits on social media or a shortcut from AI summary.'

[01:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So that\'s why we built Mark. A better way for you to engage with your&nbsp; literature without leaving the moment. Every highlight, thought you record with Mark is an idea that you believe is worth keeping. Over time, these choices become a&nbsp; catalog of your unique knowledge,'

[02:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a portrait of your belief. And it all starts with a Mark. Mark II is available for preorder today at $159. We\'ll be shipping to North America&nbsp; first, starting Q3 of 2026.'

[02:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Mark is for readers, thinkers,&nbsp; academics, professionals, and anyone who believes ideas&nbsp; shouldn\'t be fabricated by AI. This is Mark. For ideas worth keeping.'
